tructed a much sturdier bridge  and added transitions to both sides  With the new bridge in place  pedestrians will no longer be tempted to detour  cattle have passage to pastures  and the VMI maintenance crew can safely drive its vehicles along the path  Harris and his group have also removed several gates  which will be replaced in the near future  and added 20 new signs  warning hikers about private property boundaries  parking  blocking gates  and a rare endangered plant that was recently discovered growing along the trail   It s a great place  noted John Camper   But unless you have somebody diligently checking it out  it can go from great to horrible in one storm    Chris Floyd   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Chessie Bridge Makes the Way Safe for Hikers and Grazers    Chessie Bridge Makes the Way Safe for Hikers and Grazers                skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural